---
type ExploreQ = {
  id: string;
  topic: string;
  question: string;
  answer: string;
  followUps: string[];
};

const QUESTIONS: ExploreQ[] = [
  {
    id: "the_offering",
    topic: "The offering",
    question: "What is this offering?",
    answer: `A fixed rate of 8 to 10%, paid monthly on a single contract that matures in ten years. Built on coastal real estate we own and operate, plus a long-term Bitcoin reserve.

No fund layer. No middlemen. Minimum investment is $1,000.`,
    followUps: ["bond_options", "how_rate_works", "how_to_start"],
  },
  {
    id: "what_you_own",
    topic: "The offering",
    question: "What do I actually own?",
    answer: `Three things, all real.

A signed fixed-rate contract: your rate is set the moment you invest and does not move with the market. Coastal land in the Outer Banks: 88% of Dare County is federally protected, and we already own the lots we build on. Bitcoin custodied at BitGo Bank & Trust, a U.S. federally chartered institution, with $250M of Lloyd's of London insurance.

You hold the paper. We hold the assets behind it.`,
    followUps: ["outer_banks", "bitcoin_reserve", "how_to_start"],
  },
  {
    id: "bond_options",
    topic: "The offering",
    question: "What are the lock-up options?",
    answer: `One bond, two commitment levels.

A 1-year lock-up at 8.0%, for investors who want flexibility after year one. A 3-year lock-up at 10.0%, for compounders locking in the highest rate. Every bond matures at 10 years and continues paying monthly at the same rate through maturity.

Minimum investment is $1,000. Rates are nominal annual, compounded monthly, and subject to the final Offering Circular.`,
    followUps: ["what_it_looks_like", "rollover", "how_to_start"],
  },
  {
    id: "what_it_looks_like",
    topic: "The offering",
    question: "How will I receive my returns?",
    answer: `Two ways to take that 10%, on the same $100,000 example.

Monthly income path: $833 deposited every month for the full term. No surprises. No market checks. Compound path: the same $100,000 grows to roughly $270,700 after 10 years, and $134,818 after 3.

Income to live on, or interest earning interest. Same contract either way. Illustrative only.`,
    followUps: ["bond_options", "cost_of_waiting", "how_to_start"],
  },
  {
    id: "how_rate_works",
    topic: "How it works",
    question: "How can you pay 8 to 10%?",
    answer: `It is not magic. It is structure. Four conditions stacked.

Scarce coastal land: Outer Banks prices doubled in nine years, from $311K to $622K. No fund layer: we are not a REIT, so no manager fee siphons yield before it reaches you. No leverage on the digital side: we hold Bitcoin and Ethereum and do not trade them. Founder-run: decisions are made by the person whose name is on the door.`,
    followUps: ["outer_banks", "bitcoin_reserve", "how_to_start"],
  },
  {
    id: "outer_banks",
    topic: "How it works",
    question: "What's the deal with the Outer Banks?",
    answer: `A barrier-island market with real scarcity and real receipts.

The Outer Banks is a 200-mile chain in North Carolina. Federal parks, CAMA setbacks, and septic rules hard-cap buildable inventory. Demand keeps coming: more than 5 million visitors a year, $2.1B in tourism spending in 2024, and Dare County's median price is $620K, up 16.2% year over year. 10-year appreciation has roughly doubled values.

Our build economics are plain: under $100K per lot, around $350K to build, sells for around $575K, in roughly a 10-month cycle. We buy underpriced lots, build to the comp, and sell into a supply-constrained market.`,
    followUps: ["how_rate_works", "track_record", "how_to_start"],
  },
  {
    id: "bitcoin_reserve",
    topic: "How it works",
    question: "Why also Bitcoin?",
    answer: `Bitcoin is the only digital asset with a 21 million unit hard cap written into the protocol. The scarcest monetary asset humans have built.

We accumulate it as a long-term reserve alongside our real estate operations. We do not trade it. Your bond return is not indexed to its price; it is a contractual rate paid from company cash flows.

The institutional picture has shifted. 60% of the top U.S. banks now offer Bitcoin services. 90% of Barron's top 50 RIAs allocate to it. The U.S. Strategic Bitcoin Reserve holds roughly $28B. Our reserve is custodied at BitGo Bank & Trust, a federally chartered qualified custodian, with $250M of Lloyd's of London insurance, and is audited and disclosed in our semi-annual SEC reporting.`,
    followUps: ["how_rate_works", "risks", "how_to_start"],
  },
  {
    id: "cost_of_waiting",
    topic: "Why now",
    question: "Why does waiting cost me?",
    answer: `Safe money is not safe if it is quietly losing to inflation.

Same $10,000 over 10 years, four endings. Savings at 4%: roughly $14,908. A 5-year CD at 4.5%: roughly $15,530. Private credit at 8%: roughly $22,196. Robert Ventures at 10%: roughly $27,070.

In any single year, the gap looks small. Over ten, it is the difference between treading water and nearly tripling your money. Compounding starts the day you invest, not the day you decide.`,
    followUps: ["how_to_start", "what_it_looks_like", "the_offering"],
  },
  {
    id: "objections",
    topic: "Is it safe",
    question: "What do most investors worry about?",
    answer: `Four worries we hear most. Each has a clean answer.

Is my money safe? Bonds carry risk, but the structure (real assets, no leverage, founder capital subordinate to bondholders) is built to keep that risk as low as fixed-rate yield allows.

Is 10% really real? Yes. There is no fund fee, no leverage, and no bull-market dependency hiding inside it.

Can I trust the team? 25 years of operating, 200 deals, $10M raised from private investors, and Joe Robert picks up the phone.

What if I need my money before the term ends? Choose monthly payouts to keep cash flowing, or pick the 1-year option if 3 years feels long.`,
    followUps: ["risks", "track_record", "how_to_start"],
  },
  {
    id: "risks",
    topic: "Is it safe",
    question: "What are the actual risks?",
    answer: `We would rather you not invest than invest without reading this.

These are bonds: unsecured general obligations of Robert Ventures Holdings LLC. They are not bank deposits, not FDIC insured, and not backed by any government agency. SEC qualification under Reg A Tier 2 is a disclosure review, not an endorsement.

Real risks: real-estate conditions can soften, Bitcoin can draw down 50% or more in a cycle, the strategy is concentrated in one geography and one digital asset, and bonds are generally held to maturity.

How we reduce them (not eliminate them): $750K of founder capital sits subordinate to bondholders. Annual CPA audit plus semi-annual SEC reporting. Federally chartered Bitcoin custody. A 24-property active pipeline diversified across Dare County. No founder salary from this offering. Read the Offering Circular before you invest.`,
    followUps: ["track_record", "objections", "how_to_start"],
  },
  {
    id: "track_record",
    topic: "Is it safe",
    question: "What's the track record?",
    answer: `25 years of operating, and no missed payments.

Robert Ventures is the current vehicle of a team Joe Robert has been building, operating, and investing alongside for 25 years. $150M+ AUM across the platform. 200+ properties invested in or developed. 1,500+ mortgages managed. 40+ technology investments.

For this offering specifically: $1.23M raised to date. 76 investors hand-onboarded. 100% on-time distributions. 27% investor reinvestment rate. Past performance is not an indicator of future results.`,
    followUps: ["who_runs_this", "risks", "how_to_start"],
  },
  {
    id: "who_runs_this",
    topic: "Is it safe",
    question: "Who is running this?",
    answer: `Same person, every call. Joe Robert.

25 years of experience. 200+ properties sold. $10M+ raised from private investors. 100% payments record. For 25 years, his name has been on every deal he has done, and it is on this one.

There is no committee to point to and no one else to call. The person who raises the capital is the same person who answers when you need something. Aligned by structure, not by promise.`,
    followUps: ["track_record", "objections", "how_to_start"],
  },
  {
    id: "rollover",
    topic: "Logistics",
    question: "Can I use my IRA or old 401(k)?",
    answer: `Yes. Most of our investors fund this way.

Three steps. Open or use a self-directed IRA (most accounts open in 1 to 3 days). Initiate the rollover by signing a transfer form: funds move directly from your old custodian to the new account, with no distribution, no 1099, and no taxable event. Once funds land, your IRA invests in the bond. Interest grows tax-deferred in a traditional IRA, or tax-free in a Roth.

Our team handles the paperwork with your custodian. This is general information, not tax advice. Talk to your CPA before you move funds.`,
    followUps: ["how_to_start", "bond_options", "who_runs_this"],
  },
  {
    id: "how_to_start",
    topic: "Get started",
    question: "How do I get started?",
    answer: `There are two ways to begin.

Open your account to invest directly: choose your bond term and amount, connect your funding source, and our team guides you through the rest. Or schedule a 10-minute call with the team to talk through the right fit for your situation first.

Both paths lead to the same offering.`,
    followUps: ["bond_options", "objections", "risks"],
  },
];

const STARTERS = ["the_offering", "how_rate_works", "how_to_start"];
const NEXT_STEPS_AFTER = 2;
const ACCOUNT_HREF = "https://invest.robertventures.com/";
const ACCOUNT_LABEL = "Create your account";
const CALL_HREF = "/offer/book-call";
const CALL_LABEL = "Book a 10-minute call";

const questionsJson = JSON.stringify(QUESTIONS);
const startersJson = JSON.stringify(STARTERS);
---

<section class="explore" aria-label="Presentation, in your own order">
  <div class="explore__inner">
    <header class="explore__intro">
      <p class="explore__eyebrow">Presentation</p>
      <h1 class="explore__title">The presentation, <em>in your own order.</em></h1>

      <div class="explore-video">
        <div class="explore-video__container">
          <mux-player
            id="explore-mux-player"
            playback-id="zcQwBRwPYkk7H68jKSAKzUtBLukN4yls02dvyVv4TrP00"
            env-key="hr9aevib299lcvfdoip01jd60"
            preload="metadata"
            stream-type="on-demand"
            max-resolution="1080p"
            rendition-order="desc"
            poster="https://image.mux.com/zcQwBRwPYkk7H68jKSAKzUtBLukN4yls02dvyVv4TrP00/thumbnail.png?width=214&height=121&time=5"
            placeholder="https://image.mux.com/zcQwBRwPYkk7H68jKSAKzUtBLukN4yls02dvyVv4TrP00/thumbnail.webp?time=5&width=16"
            muted
            playsinline
            default-show-captions
          ></mux-player>
          <div class="explore-video__overlay" id="explore-mux-overlay" role="button" tabindex="0">
            <div class="explore-video__overlay-pill">
              <svg
                class="explore-video__overlay-icon explore-video__overlay-icon--unmute"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                aria-hidden="true"
                focusable="false"
              >
                <path
                  d="M16.5 12c0-1.77-1.02-3.29-2.5-4.03v2.21l2.45 2.45c.03-.2.05-.41.05-.63zm2.5 0c0 .94-.2 1.82-.54 2.64l1.51 1.51C20.63 14.91 21 13.5 21 12c0-4.28-2.99-7.86-7-8.77v2.06c2.89.86 5 3.54 5 6.71zM4.27 3L3 4.27 7.73 9H3v6h4l5 5v-6.73l4.25 4.25c-.67.52-1.42.93-2.25 1.18v2.06c1.38-.31 2.63-.95 3.69-1.81L19.73 21 21 19.73l-9-9L4.27 3zM12 4L9.91 6.09 12 8.18V4z"
                  fill="#ffffff"></path>
              </svg>
              <svg
                class="explore-video__overlay-icon explore-video__overlay-icon--play"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                aria-hidden="true"
                focusable="false"
              >
                <path d="M8 5v14l11-7z" fill="#ffffff"></path>
              </svg>
              <span class="explore-video__overlay-text explore-video__overlay-text--unmute">
                Your video is playing. Click to unmute.
              </span>
              <span class="explore-video__overlay-text explore-video__overlay-text--play">
                Click to play
              </span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="explore__lede">
        Tap any question. Each answer suggests where to go next. Stop whenever it's clear.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div
      class="explore__transcript"
      id="explore-transcript"
      role="log"
      aria-live="polite"
      aria-label="Conversation"
      data-questions={questionsJson}
      data-starters={startersJson}
      data-next-steps-after={String(NEXT_STEPS_AFTER)}
      data-account-href={ACCOUNT_HREF}
      data-account-label={ACCOUNT_LABEL}
      data-call-href={CALL_HREF}
      data-call-label={CALL_LABEL}
    >
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="explore-stickycta" role="region" aria-label="Next steps" data-cta-bar>
    <div class="explore-stickycta__inner">
      <a
        class="explore-stickycta__btn explore-stickycta__btn--primary"
        href={ACCOUNT_HREF}
        data-explore-cta
        data-track-cta="create_account"
        data-track-location="explore_sticky"
      >
        {ACCOUNT_LABEL}
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style is:global>
  /* All selectors are namespaced under .explore so they don't leak.
     Global is required because the transcript is built with createElement
     and Astro's scoped attributes are not added to dynamic elements. */

  .explore {
    --ink: #0f1419;
    --ink-soft: #3a4148;
    --ink-mute: #6b7178;
    --ink-faint: #b6bbc1;
    --paper: #fafaf7;
    --paper-2: #ffffff;
    --rule: rgba(15, 20, 25, 0.08);
    --rule-strong: rgba(15, 20, 25, 0.14);
    --accent: var(--green-brand, #67b78f);
    --accent-deep: var(--green-dark, #2b6b47);
    --accent-tint: rgba(103, 183, 143, 0.08);
    --ease-out: cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
    --ease-in-out: cubic-bezier(0.65, 0, 0.35, 1);

    background: var(--paper);
    min-height: 70vh;
    padding-bottom: 24px;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-feature-settings: "kern", "liga", "ss01";
    font-variant-numeric: lining-nums;
  }

  .explore__inner {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 28px 24px 24px;
  }

  .explore__intro {
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .explore__eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }

  .explore__title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(32px, 6vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .explore__title em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .explore__lede {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 520px;
  }

  /* === Editorial intro video (mirrors IntroFounderVideo) === */

  .explore-video {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 480px;
    margin: 28px auto 28px;
  }

  .explore-video__container {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #152429;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .explore-video__container mux-player {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
    --media-object-fit: cover;
    --media-object-position: center;
    --time-range: none;
  }

  .explore-video__container mux-player[mediaisfullscreen] {
    --time-range: initial;
  }

  .explore-video__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    display: none;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    cursor: pointer;
    z-index: 3;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);
  }

  .explore-video__overlay.is-active {
    display: flex;
  }

  .explore-video__overlay:focus-visible {
    outline: 3px solid #ffffff;
    outline-offset: -4px;
  }

  .explore-video__overlay-pill {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.65);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.625rem 1rem 0.625rem 0.75rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    color: #ffffff;
    font-family: "Roboto", sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    white-space: nowrap;
    animation: explore-mux-pill-glow 2.4s ease-in-out infinite;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .explore-video__overlay-icon {
    width: 22px;
    height: 22px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .explore-video__overlay-icon--play {
    display: none;
    margin-left: 2px;
  }

  .explore-video__overlay-text--play {
    display: none;
  }

  .explore-video__overlay.is-play-mode .explore-video__overlay-icon--unmute,
  .explore-video__overlay.is-play-mode .explore-video__overlay-text--unmute {
    display: none;
  }

  .explore-video__overlay.is-play-mode .explore-video__overlay-icon--play,
  .explore-video__overlay.is-play-mode .explore-video__overlay-text--play {
    display: inline-block;
  }

  @keyframes explore-mux-pill-glow {
    0%,
    100% {
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(103, 183, 143, 0.55);
    }
    70% {
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 14px rgba(103, 183, 143, 0);
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .explore-video__overlay-pill {
      animation: none;
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .explore-video {
      max-width: 520px;
      margin: 36px auto 36px;
    }
    .explore-video__overlay-pill {
      padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem 0.75rem 1rem;
      font-size: 0.9375rem;
    }
    .explore-video__overlay-icon {
      width: 24px;
      height: 24px;
    }
  }

  .explore__transcript {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  /* === Exchange (one Q&A unit) === */

  .explore .exchange {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 40px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    scroll-margin-top: 80px;
  }

  .explore .exchange:first-child {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 8px;
  }

  .explore .exchange--starter {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
    padding-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .explore .exchange--starter .options {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .explore .exchange__q {
    display: flex;
    gap: 14px;
    align-items: baseline;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(22px, 3.4vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--ink);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .explore .exchange__q-mark {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--accent-deep);
    font-size: 0.78em;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 1;
    transform: translateY(0.06em);
  }

  .explore .exchange__a {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .explore .exchange__a p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .explore .exchange__a p + p {
    margin-top: 14px;
  }

  /* Inline CTA block under a high-intent answer (e.g. "How do I get started?") */
  .explore .exchange__cta {
    margin-top: 28px;
    scroll-margin-top: 80px;
  }

  /* === Options list (command-palette rows) === */

  .explore .options {
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  .explore .options__label {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    margin: 0 0 4px;
  }

  .explore .options__list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .explore .option {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .explore .option__btn {
    appearance: none;
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    width: 100%;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 18px 4px 18px 0;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 17px;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--ink);
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
    transition:
      color 180ms var(--ease-out),
      padding-left 220ms var(--ease-out);
  }

  .explore .option:last-child .option__btn {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .explore .option__btn:hover {
    color: var(--accent-deep);
    padding-left: 6px;
  }

  .explore .option__btn:focus-visible {
    outline: none;
    color: var(--accent-deep);
    padding-left: 6px;
  }

  .explore .option__btn:focus-visible::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
  }

  .explore .option__arrow {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1;
    transition:
      transform 220ms var(--ease-out),
      color 180ms var(--ease-out);
  }

  .explore .option__btn:hover .option__arrow,
  .explore .option__btn:focus-visible .option__arrow {
    color: var(--accent);
    transform: translateX(6px);
  }

  .explore .options__browse {
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  /* Quiet variant used after the "How do I get started?" answer: only renders
     the browse-all link, with extra breathing room so the CTAs above own the
     viewport. */
  .explore .options--quiet {
    margin-top: 40px;
    padding-top: 20px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .explore .options--quiet .options__browse {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .explore .options--quiet .options__browse-btn {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }

  .explore .options--quiet .options__browse-btn:hover {
    color: var(--ink-mute);
  }

  .explore .options__browse-btn {
    appearance: none;
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    cursor: pointer;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    transition: color 180ms var(--ease-out);
  }

  .explore .options__browse-btn:hover {
    color: var(--accent-deep);
  }

  .explore .options__browse-btn::after {
    content: "→";
    transition: transform 220ms var(--ease-out);
  }

  .explore .options__browse-btn:hover::after {
    transform: translateX(4px);
  }

  /* === Inline next-steps (quiet companion, never interrupts) === */

  .explore .next-steps {
    margin-top: 28px;
    padding: 24px 22px 22px;
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 12px;
    scroll-margin-top: 80px;
  }

  .explore .next-steps__label {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }

  .explore .next-steps__hint {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    margin: 16px 0 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* === Canonical dual-CTA (matches PresDualCTA design system) === */

  .explore-dual-cta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .explore-dual-cta a {
    text-decoration: none;
    text-align: center;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 17px;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 100%;
    padding: 14px 20px;
    width: 100%;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    transition:
      background-color 0.2s ease,
      border-color 0.2s ease,
      color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .explore-dual-cta__primary {
    background-color: var(--green-brand);
    border: 1px solid var(--green-brand);
    color: #ffffff;
  }

  .explore-dual-cta__primary:hover,
  .explore-dual-cta__primary:active {
    background-color: var(--green-hover);
    border-color: var(--green-hover);
    color: #ffffff;
  }

  .explore-dual-cta__secondary {
    background-color: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--text-heading);
    color: var(--text-heading);
  }

  .explore-dual-cta__secondary:hover,
  .explore-dual-cta__secondary:active {
    background-color: var(--text-heading);
    color: #ffffff;
  }

  /* Single-CTA variant: keep the button at a sensible width, centered */

  .explore-dual-cta--single {
    align-items: center;
  }

  .explore-dual-cta--single a {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 340px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .explore-dual-cta {
      flex-direction: row;
    }
    .explore-dual-cta a {
      flex: 1;
    }
  }

  /* === Browse-all: "new thread" treatment === */

  .explore .browse {
    padding: 64px 0 8px;
    margin-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    scroll-margin-top: 80px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .explore .browse__chapter {
    position: absolute;
    top: -10px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    background: var(--paper);
    padding: 0 14px;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent-deep);
  }

  .explore .browse__intro {
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0 auto 48px;
    max-width: 480px;
  }

  .explore .browse__title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 34px);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  .explore .browse__lede {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .explore .browse__group + .browse__group {
    margin-top: 44px;
  }

  .explore .browse__group-title {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    margin: 0 0 4px;
  }

  /* === Sticky CTA bar (matches PresStickyCTA: white fade + dual CTA) === */

  .explore-stickycta {
    position: fixed;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    z-index: 50;
    background: linear-gradient(
      to top,
      #ffffff 0%,
      #ffffff 55%,
      rgba(255, 255, 255, 0) 100%
    );
    padding: 32px 1rem calc(14px + env(safe-area-inset-bottom));
    pointer-events: none;
    transition: opacity 280ms var(--ease-out), transform 280ms var(--ease-out);
  }

  .explore-stickycta[data-hidden="true"] {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(8px);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .explore-stickycta__inner {
    max-width: 420px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 8px;
    width: 100%;
    pointer-events: auto;
  }

  .explore-stickycta__btn {
    flex: 1;
    text-decoration: none;
    text-align: center;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-family: "Roboto", sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 100%;
    padding: 12px 12px;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    transition:
      background-color 0.2s ease,
      border-color 0.2s ease,
      color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .explore-stickycta__btn--primary {
    background-color: var(--green-brand);
    border: 1px solid var(--green-brand);
    color: #ffffff;
    animation: explore-stickycta-pulse-primary 2.6s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  .explore-stickycta__btn--primary:hover,
  .explore-stickycta__btn--primary:active {
    background-color: var(--green-hover);
    border-color: var(--green-hover);
    color: #ffffff;
  }

  .explore-stickycta__btn--ghost {
    background-color: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--text-heading);
    color: var(--text-heading);
    animation: explore-stickycta-pulse-ghost 2.6s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  .explore-stickycta__btn--ghost:hover,
  .explore-stickycta__btn--ghost:active {
    background-color: var(--text-heading);
    color: #ffffff;
  }

  @keyframes explore-stickycta-pulse-primary {
    0%,
    100% {
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(103, 183, 143, 0.55);
    }
    70% {
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 8px rgba(103, 183, 143, 0);
    }
  }

  @keyframes explore-stickycta-pulse-ghost {
    0%,
    100% {
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.22);
    }
    70% {
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 8px rgba(26, 26, 26, 0);
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .explore-stickycta {
      padding: 40px 2rem calc(16px + env(safe-area-inset-bottom));
    }
    .explore-stickycta__inner {
      gap: 12px;
    }
    .explore-stickycta__btn {
      font-size: 16px;
      padding: 14px 20px;
    }
  }

  /* === Motion === */

  .explore .reveal {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(8px);
    animation: explore-reveal 480ms var(--ease-out) forwards;
  }

  .explore .reveal[data-delay="1"] {
    animation-delay: 80ms;
  }
  .explore .reveal[data-delay="2"] {
    animation-delay: 180ms;
  }
  .explore .reveal[data-delay="3"] {
    animation-delay: 280ms;
  }

  @keyframes explore-reveal {
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .explore .reveal,
    .explore .reveal[data-delay] {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: none;
      animation: none;
    }
    .explore .option__btn,
    .explore .option__arrow,
    .explore-stickycta,
    .explore-stickycta__btn--primary,
    .explore-stickycta__btn--ghost {
      transition: none;
      animation: none;
    }
  }

  /* === Responsive === */

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .explore__inner {
      padding: 44px 32px 32px;
    }
    .explore__intro {
      margin-bottom: 36px;
    }
    .explore .exchange {
      padding: 56px 0;
    }
    .explore .exchange__a {
      font-size: 18px;
    }
    .explore .option__btn {
      font-size: 18px;
      padding: 22px 4px 22px 0;
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 1136px) {
    .explore__inner {
      padding-top: 64px;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  type ExploreQ = {
    id: string;
    topic: string;
    question: string;
    answer: string;
    followUps: string[];
  };

  function gaTrack(eventName: string, eventData: Record<string, unknown> = {}) {
    const dl = (window as unknown as { dataLayer?: Array<Record<string, unknown>> }).dataLayer;
    if (dl) dl.push({ event: eventName, ...eventData });
  }
  function phTrack(eventName: string, eventData: Record<string, unknown> = {}) {
    const ph = (window as unknown as {
      posthogTrack?: (n: string, p?: Record<string, unknown>) => void;
    }).posthogTrack;
    if (typeof ph === "function") ph(eventName, eventData);
  }
  function phSetPerson(props: Record<string, unknown>) {
    const ph = (window as unknown as { posthogSetPerson?: (p: Record<string, unknown>) => void })
      .posthogSetPerson;
    if (typeof ph === "function") ph(props);
  }

  function escapeHtml(s: string): string {
    return s
      .replace(/&/g, "&amp;")
      .replace(/</g, "&lt;")
      .replace(/>/g, "&gt;")
      .replace(/"/g, "&quot;")
      .replace(/'/g, "&#39;");
  }

  function paragraphsHtml(text: string): string {
    return text
      .trim()
      .split(/\n{2,}/)
      .map((p) => `<p>${escapeHtml(p.trim()).replace(/\n/g, "<br />")}</p>`)
      .join("");
  }

  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
    const transcript = document.getElementById("explore-transcript");
    const ctaBar = document.querySelector("[data-cta-bar]") as HTMLElement | null;
    if (!transcript) return;

    const QUESTIONS: ExploreQ[] = JSON.parse(transcript.dataset.questions || "[]");
    const STARTERS: string[] = JSON.parse(transcript.dataset.starters || "[]");
    const NEXT_STEPS_AFTER = Number(transcript.dataset.nextStepsAfter || "4");
    const ACCOUNT_HREF = transcript.dataset.accountHref || "https://invest.robertventures.com/";
    const ACCOUNT_LABEL = transcript.dataset.accountLabel || "Create your account";
    const CALL_HREF = transcript.dataset.callHref || "/offer/book-call";
    const CALL_LABEL = transcript.dataset.callLabel || "Book a 10-minute call";

    const byId = new Map<string, ExploreQ>(QUESTIONS.map((q) => [q.id, q]));

    const state = {
      asked: new Set<string>(),
      count: 0,
      started: false,
      currentOptionsEl: null as HTMLElement | null,
    };

    function append(node: HTMLElement, opts: { scroll?: boolean; focus?: boolean } = {}) {
      const { scroll = true, focus = false } = opts;
      transcript!.appendChild(node);
      requestAnimationFrame(() => {
        if (scroll) node.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth", block: "start" });
        if (focus) {
          const firstBtn = node.querySelector(
            "button.option__btn"
          ) as HTMLButtonElement | null;
          if (firstBtn) firstBtn.focus({ preventScroll: true });
        }
      });
    }

    function buildNextSteps(): HTMLElement {
      const aside = document.createElement("aside");
      aside.className = "next-steps";
      aside.innerHTML = `
        <p class="next-steps__label">When you're ready</p>
        <div class="explore-dual-cta explore-dual-cta--single">
          <a
            class="explore-dual-cta__primary"
            href="${escapeHtml(ACCOUNT_HREF)}"
            data-explore-cta
            data-track-cta="create_account"
            data-track-location="explore_inline"
          >${escapeHtml(ACCOUNT_LABEL)}</a>
        </div>
        <p class="next-steps__hint">Or keep exploring. The questions above are still open.</p>
      `;
      return aside;
    }

    function buildOptionsList(
      ids: string[],
      label: string,
      source: string,
      includeBrowse: boolean = true
    ): HTMLElement {
      const wrap = document.createElement("div");
      wrap.className = "options reveal";
      wrap.setAttribute("data-delay", "3");

      const lbl = document.createElement("p");
      lbl.className = "options__label";
      lbl.textContent = label;
      wrap.appendChild(lbl);

      const list = document.createElement("ul");
      list.className = "options__list";

      ids.forEach((id) => {
        const q = byId.get(id);
        if (!q) return;
        const li = document.createElement("li");
        li.className = "option";
        const btn = document.createElement("button");
        btn.type = "button";
        btn.className = "option__btn";
        btn.dataset.questionId = id;
        btn.dataset.source = source;
        btn.innerHTML = `<span class="option__label">${escapeHtml(q.question)}</span><span class="option__arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>`;
        li.appendChild(btn);
        list.appendChild(li);
      });

      wrap.appendChild(list);

      if (state.count >= NEXT_STEPS_AFTER) {
        wrap.appendChild(buildNextSteps());
      }

      if (includeBrowse) {
        const browseWrap = document.createElement("div");
        browseWrap.className = "options__browse";
        const browseBtn = document.createElement("button");
        browseBtn.type = "button";
        browseBtn.className = "options__browse-btn";
        browseBtn.dataset.action = "browse-all";
        browseBtn.textContent = "Or browse all topics";
        browseWrap.appendChild(browseBtn);
        wrap.appendChild(browseWrap);
      }

      return wrap;
    }

    function renderStarter() {
      const exchange = document.createElement("div");
      exchange.className = "exchange exchange--starter";
      const opts = buildOptionsList(STARTERS, "Where would you like to start?", "starter", true);
      exchange.appendChild(opts);
      state.currentOptionsEl = opts;
      // No scroll, no focus on initial render — let the user read the intro first.
      append(exchange, { scroll: false, focus: false });
    }

    function clearOldOptions() {
      // Remove the previous options block so the chain stays clean.
      // (We keep all answered Q&A, only the now-stale option list disappears.)
      if (state.currentOptionsEl && state.currentOptionsEl.parentElement) {
        state.currentOptionsEl.parentElement.removeChild(state.currentOptionsEl);
        state.currentOptionsEl = null;
      }
    }

    function renderExchange(q: ExploreQ) {
      const exchange = document.createElement("article");
      exchange.className = "exchange";
      exchange.setAttribute("data-question-id", q.id);

      const qHeading = document.createElement("h2");
      qHeading.className = "exchange__q reveal";
      qHeading.setAttribute("data-delay", "1");
      qHeading.innerHTML = `<span class="exchange__q-mark" aria-hidden="true">Q.</span><span>${escapeHtml(q.question)}</span>`;
      exchange.appendChild(qHeading);

      const answer = document.createElement("div");
      answer.className = "exchange__a reveal";
      answer.setAttribute("data-delay", "2");
      answer.innerHTML = paragraphsHtml(q.answer);
      exchange.appendChild(answer);

      // Clear-intent answer: surface both CTAs inline so the user can act
      // immediately without scrolling or hunting through follow-ups. On this
      // node we deliberately suppress the "People also ask" list and the
      // "When you're ready" panel so the dual CTA carries the focus alone.
      if (q.id === "how_to_start") {
        const ctaWrap = document.createElement("div");
        ctaWrap.className = "exchange__cta reveal";
        ctaWrap.setAttribute("data-delay", "3");
        ctaWrap.innerHTML = `
          <div class="explore-dual-cta">
            <a
              class="explore-dual-cta__primary"
              href="${escapeHtml(ACCOUNT_HREF)}"
              data-explore-cta
              data-track-cta="create_account"
              data-track-location="explore_get_started"
            >${escapeHtml(ACCOUNT_LABEL)}</a>
            <a
              class="explore-dual-cta__secondary"
              href="${escapeHtml(CALL_HREF)}"
              data-explore-cta
              data-track-cta="book_call"
              data-track-location="explore_get_started"
            >${escapeHtml(CALL_LABEL)}</a>
          </div>
        `;
        exchange.appendChild(ctaWrap);

        const remainingCount = QUESTIONS.filter((qq) => !state.asked.has(qq.id)).length;
        const quietWrap = document.createElement("div");
        quietWrap.className = "options reveal options--quiet";
        quietWrap.setAttribute("data-delay", "3");
        if (remainingCount > 0) {
          const browseWrap = document.createElement("div");
          browseWrap.className = "options__browse";
          const browseBtn = document.createElement("button");
          browseBtn.type = "button";
          browseBtn.className = "options__browse-btn";
          browseBtn.dataset.action = "browse-all";
          browseBtn.textContent = "Or browse all topics";
          browseWrap.appendChild(browseBtn);
          quietWrap.appendChild(browseWrap);
        }
        exchange.appendChild(quietWrap);
        state.currentOptionsEl = quietWrap;

        append(exchange, { scroll: true, focus: false });
        return;
      }

      const followUps = q.followUps.filter((fid) => !state.asked.has(fid));
      let opts: HTMLElement;
      if (followUps.length > 0) {
        opts = buildOptionsList(followUps, "People also ask", "followup", true);
      } else {
        opts = buildOptionsList(
          QUESTIONS.filter((qq) => !state.asked.has(qq.id))
            .slice(0, 3)
            .map((qq) => qq.id),
          "More you can explore",
          "followup",
          true
        );
      }
      exchange.appendChild(opts);
      state.currentOptionsEl = opts;

      append(exchange, { scroll: true, focus: true });
    }

    function renderBrowseAll() {
      clearOldOptions();
      const remaining = QUESTIONS.filter((q) => !state.asked.has(q.id));

      if (remaining.length === 0) {
        const aside = buildNextSteps();
        aside.classList.add("reveal");
        transcript!.appendChild(aside);
        state.currentOptionsEl = aside;
        requestAnimationFrame(() => {
          aside.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth", block: "start" });
        });
        return;
      }

      const browse = document.createElement("section");
      browse.className = "browse reveal";
      browse.setAttribute("data-delay", "1");
      browse.setAttribute("aria-label", "Start a new thread");

      const chapter = document.createElement("span");
      chapter.className = "browse__chapter";
      chapter.textContent = "New thread";
      browse.appendChild(chapter);

      const intro = document.createElement("div");
      intro.className = "browse__intro";
      intro.innerHTML = `
        <h2 class="browse__title">Start a new thread.</h2>
        <p class="browse__lede">Pick anywhere. The conversation continues from there.</p>
      `;
      browse.appendChild(intro);

      const grouped = new Map<string, ExploreQ[]>();
      remaining.forEach((q) => {
        const arr = grouped.get(q.topic) || [];
        arr.push(q);
        grouped.set(q.topic, arr);
      });

      grouped.forEach((items, topic) => {
        const group = document.createElement("div");
        group.className = "browse__group";

        const gt = document.createElement("p");
        gt.className = "browse__group-title";
        gt.textContent = topic;
        group.appendChild(gt);

        const list = document.createElement("ul");
        list.className = "options__list";
        items.forEach((q) => {
          const li = document.createElement("li");
          li.className = "option";
          const btn = document.createElement("button");
          btn.type = "button";
          btn.className = "option__btn";
          btn.dataset.questionId = q.id;
          btn.dataset.source = "browse_all";
          btn.innerHTML = `<span class="option__label">${escapeHtml(q.question)}</span><span class="option__arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>`;
          li.appendChild(btn);
          list.appendChild(li);
        });
        group.appendChild(list);
        browse.appendChild(group);
      });

      if (state.count >= NEXT_STEPS_AFTER) {
        browse.appendChild(buildNextSteps());
      }

      transcript!.appendChild(browse);
      state.currentOptionsEl = browse;
      requestAnimationFrame(() => {
        browse.scrollIntoView({ behavior: "smooth", block: "start" });
        const firstBtn = browse.querySelector("button.option__btn") as HTMLButtonElement | null;
        if (firstBtn) firstBtn.focus({ preventScroll: true });
      });
    }

    function selectQuestion(id: string, source: string) {
      const q = byId.get(id);
      if (!q) return;

      if (!state.started) {
        state.started = true;
        gaTrack("explore_started");
        phTrack("explore_started");
      }

      clearOldOptions();
      state.asked.add(id);
      state.count += 1;

      renderExchange(q);

      gaTrack("explore_question_selected", {
        question_id: id,
        source,
        position_in_session: state.count,
      });
      phTrack("explore_question_selected", {
        question_id: id,
        topic: q.topic,
        source,
        position_in_session: state.count,
      });
      phSetPerson({ explore_last_topic: q.topic, explore_last_question: id });
    }

    transcript.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
      const target = e.target as HTMLElement | null;
      if (!target) return;
      const browseBtn = target.closest('button[data-action="browse-all"]') as HTMLButtonElement | null;
      if (browseBtn) {
        renderBrowseAll();
        return;
      }
      const btn = target.closest("button.option__btn") as HTMLButtonElement | null;
      if (!btn || !transcript.contains(btn)) return;
      const id = btn.dataset.questionId;
      const source = btn.dataset.source || "unknown";
      if (id) selectQuestion(id, source);
    });

    document.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
      const target = e.target as HTMLElement | null;
      if (!target) return;
      const link = target.closest("[data-explore-cta]") as HTMLElement | null;
      if (!link) return;
      const location = link.dataset.trackLocation || "unknown";
      const ctaType = link.dataset.trackCta || "unknown";
      gaTrack("explore_cta_clicked", { location, cta_type: ctaType });
      phTrack("explore_cta_clicked", {
        location,
        cta_type: ctaType,
        questions_viewed: state.count,
      });
    });

    // Slide the sticky CTA bar out of view while an inline next-steps panel
    // is on screen, so the two CTA surfaces don't compete with each other.
    if (ctaBar && "IntersectionObserver" in window) {
      const io = new IntersectionObserver(
        (entries) => {
          entries.forEach((entry) => {
            if (entry.target.classList.contains("next-steps")) {
              ctaBar.dataset.hidden = entry.isIntersecting ? "true" : "false";
            }
          });
        },
        { rootMargin: "0px 0px -30% 0px", threshold: 0.1 }
      );
      const observed = new WeakSet<Element>();
      const mo = new MutationObserver(() => {
        document.querySelectorAll(".explore .next-steps").forEach((el) => {
          if (!observed.has(el)) {
            io.observe(el);
            observed.add(el);
          }
        });
      });
      mo.observe(transcript, { childList: true, subtree: true });
    }

    let summarySent = false;
    function sendSummary() {
      if (summarySent || state.count === 0) return;
      summarySent = true;
      const topics = new Set<string>();
      state.asked.forEach((id) => {
        const q = byId.get(id);
        if (q) topics.add(q.topic);
      });
      const payload = {
        questions_viewed: state.count,
        topics_touched: Array.from(topics),
      };
      gaTrack("explore_session_summary", payload);
      phTrack("explore_session_summary", payload);
    }
    window.addEventListener("pagehide", sendSummary);
    window.addEventListener("beforeunload", sendSummary);

    renderStarter();
    setupExploreVideo();
  });

  // Mirrors IntroFounderVideo: muted autoplay when the player is in view, with
  // a one-shot unmute pill. After engagement, Mux's native UI takes over.
  function setupExploreVideo() {
    const player = document.getElementById("explore-mux-player") as HTMLMediaElement | null;
    const overlay = document.getElementById("explore-mux-overlay");
    if (!player) return;

    let autoplayState: "pending" | "trying" | "playing" | "failed" = "pending";
    let isAutoplayPlay = false;
    let engaged = false;

    function showOverlayUnmuteMode() {
      if (!overlay) return;
      overlay.classList.add("is-active");
      overlay.classList.remove("is-play-mode");
      overlay.setAttribute("aria-label", "Your video is playing. Click to unmute.");
    }
    function showOverlayPlayMode() {
      if (!overlay) return;
      overlay.classList.add("is-active", "is-play-mode");
      overlay.setAttribute("aria-label", "Click to play");
    }
    function dismissOverlay() {
      if (!overlay) return;
      overlay.classList.remove("is-active");
    }

    function attemptAutoplay() {
      if (autoplayState !== "pending") return;
      autoplayState = "trying";
      try {
        player!.muted = true;
      } catch (e) {}
      isAutoplayPlay = true;
      const promise = player!.play();
      if (promise && typeof promise.then === "function") {
        promise
          .then(() => {
            autoplayState = "playing";
            if (!engaged) showOverlayUnmuteMode();
          })
          .catch(() => {
            isAutoplayPlay = false;
            autoplayState = "failed";
            if (!engaged) showOverlayPlayMode();
          });
      } else {
        autoplayState = "playing";
        if (!engaged) showOverlayUnmuteMode();
      }
    }

    function engageFromOverlay(e: Event) {
      if (!overlay || !overlay.classList.contains("is-active")) return;
      e.preventDefault();
      e.stopPropagation();
      const isPlayMode = overlay.classList.contains("is-play-mode");
      try {
        player!.muted = false;
      } catch (err) {}
      if (isPlayMode) {
        const result = player!.play();
        if (result && typeof result.catch === "function") result.catch(() => {});
      }
      dismissOverlay();
    }

    if (overlay) {
      overlay.addEventListener("click", engageFromOverlay);
      overlay.addEventListener("keydown", (e) => {
        const ke = e as KeyboardEvent;
        if (ke.key === "Enter" || ke.key === " ") engageFromOverlay(e);
      });
    }

    player.addEventListener("play", () => {
      const wasAutoplay = isAutoplayPlay;
      isAutoplayPlay = false;
      if (!wasAutoplay) {
        engaged = true;
        dismissOverlay();
      }
    });

    player.addEventListener("volumechange", () => {
      if (engaged) return;
      if (player.muted) return;
      engaged = true;
      dismissOverlay();
    });

    if ("IntersectionObserver" in window) {
      const videoIo = new IntersectionObserver(
        (entries) => {
          entries.forEach((entry) => {
            if (entry.isIntersecting) {
              if (autoplayState === "pending") {
                attemptAutoplay();
              } else if (autoplayState === "playing" && player.paused && !engaged) {
                isAutoplayPlay = true;
                const result = player.play();
                if (result && typeof result.catch === "function") {
                  result.catch(() => {
                    isAutoplayPlay = false;
                  });
                }
              }
            } else if (!player.paused) {
              player.pause();
            }
          });
        },
        { threshold: 0, rootMargin: "0px 0px 40% 0px" }
      );
      videoIo.observe(player);
    }
  }
</script>
